import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react"; import { useNavigate, useParams } from 'react-router-dom' import axios from "axios"; import { TableB, TbodyB, Tdb, ThB, TheadB, TrbB, TrhB } from "../../component/ui/table"; const URI = "http://localhost:8000/usuarios/" const URIS = "http://localhost:8000/valUser" const ShowListUser = () => { const[ dataD, setData ] = useState([]) const[ staUser, setStaUser ] = useState('') const[ cargUser, setCargUser ] = useState('') const[ refrTab, setFrTab] = useState(false) const navigate = useNavigate() const {id} = useParams() const valData = async () => { try{ const resSt = await axios.get(URIS) if(resSt.status == 200){ setStaUser(resSt.data.statusUser) setCargUser(resSt.data.cargoId) } }catch(e){ console.error(e) } } const getdata = async () => { const docs = [] try{ if(cargUser){ console.log(cargUser) const params = { key1: cargUser, } const res = await axios.get(URI,{ params }) console.log(res.data) res.data.forEach(element => { docs.push({'id': element.id, 'Name':element.Name, 'lastName':element.lastName, 'tel':element.tel, 'email':element.email, 'andress':element.andress, 'user':element.user}) }) setData(docs) } }catch(e){ console.error(e) } } useEffect(() => { valData() }, []) useEffect(() => { getdata() },[cargUser]) return( <>
